# Multi-Environment File Structure Example
# This shows the new organization of environment variables

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY LAYERS:
# =============================================================================

# ~/.env_tokens (PRIVATE GIST - Most Sensitive)
# - Personal API keys, tokens, credentials
# - GitHub personal access tokens
# - AWS keys, database passwords
# - Never commit to git, stored in encrypted private gist

# ~/.env_ai (CAN BE SHARED/GIST)
# - AI service configurations  
# - Model settings, API endpoints
# - LiteLLM configs, Ollama settings
# - Safe to share in team gist

# ~/.env_docker (CAN BE SHARED/GIST)
# - Container configurations
# - Port mappings, network settings
# - Docker registry configs (without credentials)
# - Safe to share in team gist

# ~/.env_repos (CAN BE SHARED/GIST)  
# - Repository paths and URLs
# - Project workspace configurations
# - Git settings (without tokens)
# - Safe to share in team gist

# ~/.env_local (NEVER SYNCED)
# - Machine-specific overrides
# - Local development preferences  
# - Network configurations
# - Stays only on local machine

# =============================================================================
# USAGE EXAMPLES:
# =============================================================================

# Personal tokens (keep in ~/.env_tokens):
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_personal_access_token_here
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your_openai_api_key_here
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=AKIA_your_aws_key_here

# AI configurations (can go in ~/.env_ai):
DEFAULT_MODEL=gpt-4
LITELLM_PORT=10001
OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434

# Repository paths (can go in ~/.env_repos):
CODE_DIR=/home/user/code
ZENFLOW_REPO=/home/user/code/zenflow
GITHUB_USERNAME=your_username

# Local overrides (goes in ~/.env_local):
MACHINE_NAME=dev-laptop
DEV_MODE=true
LOCAL_PORT_OFFSET=100

# =============================================================================
# LOADING ORDER (later files override earlier ones):
# =============================================================================
# 1. ~/.env_tokens    (base secrets)
# 2. ~/.env_ai        (AI configs)  
# 3. ~/.env_docker    (container configs)
# 4. ~/.env_repos     (project configs)
# 5. ~/.env_local     (local overrides)